My 600-lb Life is an American reality television series that has aired on the TLC television network since 2012. Each episode follows a year in the life of morbidly obese individuals, who usually begin the episode weighing at least 600 pounds (270 kg), and documents their attempts to reduce their weight to a healthy level. Update episodes, called "Where Are They Now?", feature one or more previous patients, picking up a year or more after their original episodes aired.

Patients are placed under the care of Iranian-American Houston surgeon Younan Nowzaradan (often referred to as simply "Dr. Now"), who first has them attempt losing weight on their own by following a strict diet, and then depending on the patient's progress may offer gastric bypass surgery or sleeve gastrectomy to further assist in weight loss.

In this video, I wanted to do something different! I decided to dive into a care package that was sent to me a few months ago that contained all VEGAN products! That got me thinking, why not go out and see what I could find in fast food that was VEGAN as well!

I made sure to use some reeses cups, kit kats, and snickers in the cookie dough mixture as well. Had a lot of fun making this one! Be sure to check out the video to see how I did!

title: THE "SUPERCHARGED" 40,000 CALORIE CHEAT DAY
description:
(Check me out on social media!) 
► Instagram: http://bit.ly/2rWyjgU
► Facebook: http://bit.ly/2sXVR3t
► Twitter: http://bit.ly/2soQEog

Just a "FAQ" for those that may be slightly confused or that may have questions after viewing the video!

There were some slight calculation errors in the video. Unfortunately, I forgot to delete the "chocolate shakes" from the MFP entry used in the video, however I forgot to account for the coconut oil used while baking the reese's bars and also the additional milk I used with the final meal. Thankfully, when it was all said and done I was over 40,000 calories! 

This one was INSANE! Definitely the biggest day of eating I've EVER had. Enjoy! 

Meal 1 ► 
1 Box Cinnamon Toast Crunch 
1 Jar of Nutella 
12 Egg Omelette 
8 Tbspns Coconut Oil 
1 Apple 
1 Container Oreos 
1 Box Coco Puffs (Family Size) 
12 Doughnuts (Under-estimated for video) 
1/2 Jar Skippy PB 
1 Loaf Of Bread (Forgot to Input) 
1 Container Almond Milk 

Meal #2 ► 
4 McDonalds Frappes 
4 Large Fries 
4 Big Macs 
1 Large Salad 
1/2 Large Bag of Peanuts 
1 Bag of White Cheddar Cheetos 

Meal #3 ► 
6 Cinnabon Rolls 
1/2 Large Bag of Peanuts 
1 Snickers Bar 
 
Meal #4 ► 
1 Large White Rice (Couldn't find White Rice large in MFP, so Fried Rice was used instead.. calories were equal)
1 Large Orange Chicken (Even though less calories than Honey Sesame)
1 Vegetable Chow Mein 
1 Box Mac N Cheeto's 
3 Tablespoons Soy Sauce 
1/4 Jar Peanut Butter 
1 Container Reese's Dessert Bar Mix 
1 Large Egg 
8 Tablespoons Coconut Oil 
1 Pint Pistachio Pistachio 
1 Pint Reeses PB Cup 
1 Container Vanilla Almond Milk

title: GOODBYE YOUTUBE
description:
If you want to support the channel, and want me to help me get back on my feet. Click HERE! ►
http://bit.ly/2iLjMC4


As I said in the video everyone, I really do not like asking for help in situations like this. But anything does help at this point. I have two further videos uploaded (scheduled) for the next week, apart from that, It’ll be quite sometime before I am back to making videos (probably over a few months). 
There was over $8,000 worth of equipment stolen from my car three days ago (almost $9,000), which is going to be partially covered under my renters insurance. However there still is a tremendous gap, one that I (as a recent graduate) will have a hard time making up. I don't like asking for help, but I do enjoy what I do, I enjoy bringing you all content and I love what I've built over the past 4 years of doing this. Whether it's 1$ or 500$, anything will help. 

As I also mentioned in this video, I know that many will criticize me for asking for help in this situation, saying that others have it "worse off" and that there are others in desperate need. To which I've said that I will be donating any funds left over (assuming there are), to help the hurricane relief effort. Thank you to everyone who's supported me over the years and who continues to believe in me.

**ALSO**
I did not start the go fund me that is linked, the goal is not to make it to $15,000. My loyal subscriber that started the gofundme did so out of the goodness of her heart and wasn't aware of a set in stone "goal". I'll need about $4,500 to cover what insurance does not. But anything more than that will be donated to the hurricane victims!

WELL! This challenge definitely wasn't my biggest challenge ever, but I still had some fun with it! "Electric Eats" recipes aren't ever really gigantic calorie packed food challenges, they're fun to test my "culinary skills" and to combine my love of eating lots of food into one! 

As far as the recipe for the pizza "crust" since I'll get asked a lot. I used this recipe from "Thrillest" and tailored it... up a notch. 
https://www.thrillist.com/videos/eat/nation/fried-chicken-crust-pizza-recipe

As far as the ingredients used:
- 3.5 lbs of Chicken 
- 6 Containers of Mashed Potatoes 
- Gravy 
- 3/4 Cup of Butter 
- 1 Container of Cheese 
- 8oz Vegetable Oil (for frying) 
- 1 Container of Pepperoni 
- 2 Containers of shake and bake mix 
- 2 Large Eggs 
- 3 Cups of Flour


Let me know how you guys like these and I can make more of them!

I decided to come off of my ADHD medication completely for now, I know I will have a lot wondering why I chose to come off of it AND coffee/stimulants entirely. Right now, time is everything. I figured the sooner the better, the sooner I began to get my body adapted nothing but FOOD and SLEEP the better. That is ideally how the human body should function, and most likely the reason why I'm feeling the way that I am. 

I also know that a lot will question me, and also tell me that I "seem down" or seem "unhappy". But that is entirely what happens in scenarios like this. I will say that I will NOT hide who I am, or how I'm feeling and put on a "front" for people, simply because my camera is out. I'm not fake, and never will be. This is who I am.. those who support me and who want the best for me, will realize this. Thanks all.

title: THE 60,000 CALORIE CHALLENGE
description:
(Check me out on social media!) 
► Instagram: http://bit.ly/2rWyjgU
► Facebook: http://bit.ly/2sXVR3t
► Twitter: http://bit.ly/2soQEog
► Snapchat: @ErikTheElectric 
► Strava: Erik”TheElectric”Lamkin
► GamerTag: ErikTheElectric

I never thought I'd attempt anything this dumb, but one year after the infamous "50,000 calorie challenge" I thought I'd take things up a "notch" by attempting to surpass my old 50,000 calorie video. 

**As a formal disclaimer**
I DO NOT (as it should be obviously inferred) recommend doing this for ANYONE. I'm a competitive eater and have built a relatively larger (than normal) stomach capacity to be able to tolerate large amounts of food. If an average person were to attempt something of this nature, negative consequences could come of it, for that reason I will say that you should DEFINITELY not try to do anything of this nature. 

All of the MyFitnessPal Screen shots are entirely accurate, if you want to tell me that they (or my meals) are "fake" (which are just the usual troll comments), then by all means feel free. But before you do so, please check out the numerous restaurant challenges and eating contests that I've posted on my channel. 

The video was long enough already, before I did my final edit, I had just over 1.5 hours of "Finalized" footage, therefore I needed to make even more cuts. So again, if you'd like to call anyone out for being "fake", take that into consideration. 

I did overshoot the "last meal" by a large amount, I thought I'd end with my "favorites", and well.. (I won't spoil it, heh). Also, keep in mind that when you take in calories/food/carbs of this caliber, you lose part of your mental coherency, hence why I (found it rather hilarious really) kept saying "not bad" so much. So excuse that (and the messiness during the video). And I am aware I missed one "not bad" around the middle of the video, lol.

I ended up baking my breakfast bread the night before, as referenced in the video, here's the ingredients:
- 4 Cups of Flour 
- 2 Whole Eggs 
- 100g Butter 
- 5 Tablespoons of Sugar 
- 1 Tsp Yeast

**What an INSANE challenge this was!**
I'm not used to taking in this much red meat in one sitting, I definitely learned a lot from this one. As I stated in the video I ALWAYS wanted to make my very own "pizza burger", and I'm stoked with the final product! Here's the ingredients that were used.

- 1 Double Pepperoni Medium Domino's Pizza (2,205 calories)
- 1 Mushroom Pepperoni Medium Domino's Pizza (1,800 Calories)
- 4 lbs of Ground Beef (3,800 calories)
- 2  Entire Packets of Cheddar Cheese (1,700 Calories)
- 1 Bag of Frozen Onion Rings (1,100 Calories) 
- Tomatoes (~40 Calories)
- Salad + Dressing (~200 Calories)

I was bit let down because Domino's advertised that they were doing a special discount for college graduates until the 28th, in which you'd be able to get two large 1 topping pizza's for $5.99 each, but apparently it wasn't so. But I still had a good time with this challenge nonetheless!

description:

**ONLINE COACHING AND APPAREL**  ►
http://eriktheelectric.bigcartel.com/product/8-week-nutrition-plan

I wanted to combine my love of fast food reviews AND food challenges into one series and call it "Electric Eats!". The naked chicken chips from taco bell have been getting lots of buzz lately, so I decided to try them out! Of course, I like to pull my usual shenanigans in the drive thru and have fun with the drive thru workers, if you don't like making people smile every day, that's totally cool, but I prefer to not be a grumpy human being all the time!

As far as the REVIEW goes, keep in mind that it IS still a food "review" technically. It's quite common for those who are fixated on watching strictly food challenges stumble upon food reviews, scratch their heads, get angry, and then yell at the computer screen (usually in the form of a comment) stating "STOP COMPLAINING!". I then have to respond with the above statement. 

This "challenge" clocked in at just over 10,000 calories with the buns, LOTS of extra cheese, 24 chicken "chips", 70/30 patties (350 calories per patty, an entire bag of fries, and of course a salad with dressing!

title: THE 20,000 CALORIE FRUIT AND VEGGIE CHALLENGE!
description:
Support The Channel on Patreon! ► 
https://www.patreon.com/ErikTheElectric

**ONLINE COACHING AND APPAREL**  ►
http://eriktheelectric.bigcartel.com/product/8-week-nutrition-plan

BOOM! 

Without a doubt, my most DIFFICULT challenge that I’ve ever done. I was challenged by Vegan YouTuber John Venus to do the "10,000 Calorie Fruit Challenge". So, I decided to embark upon the challenge with my own little "spin" to it! I figured there are going to be LOADS of misconceptions and of course assumptions about the particular challenge that you saw above, so a few key points.

1. Everything came from (predominately) whole food, fruits and vegetables. The "no juice rule" stayed in place, and there's a VAST difference when consuming straight juice (with little to zero satiation value) vs a DENSE and THICK shake/smoothie, which can serve as a meal replacement (in this case a few meals for some people). 
2. "But Erik! Coconuts aren't FRUITS they're NUTS!" (Please see here: http://www.thebestofrawfood.com/is-coconut-a-fruit.html)
3. "But you used coconut sugar and coconut oil?" Yes! However, this made up for around ~4-5% of overall calorie consumption. 
4. This was again, the HARDEST challenge I've ever done. Even with my 13-14lb stomach capacity, the recovery from this challenge was the hardest. You'll be seeing more of that in the vlogs to come!

**A HUGE RIDE for me!**
As I've stated before I'm currently training for a big ride coming up at the end of may. I've been meaning to get a century in before the end of the month! 

I decided to take you all with me for some "post ride eats" at a place that I used to do a bunch of "capacity training" at back in the day. Unfortuantely, I got to the location a bit later than I wanted and they closed, so I didn't get to get in as much as I'd like to, but it was still great nonetheless! (for the $25 price tag, with tip).  Everything was estimated to be around 12,000 calories, by the end of the day. Lots of carbs, oil, and sugar! 

I'm also going to be attempting to SURPASS MY OLD 50,000 CALORIE RECORD... VERY SOON! I hope you're all ready for it! Leave suggestions down below!

1. Bread (I used 70 calorie bread for this one, but you CAN find 40 calorie slices! Those are used in this recipe for macro purposes)

1. 35g Pie Crust

title: FULL DAY OF EATING (AND CYCLING) | THE "ALL SUGAR DIET"
description:
It's definitely going to be an interesting month, this has been something that I've been telling myself I've need to do for quite a long time. I'm curious to see how things will work out! 

Before I get a barrage of comments telling me that artificial sweeteners are "perfectly safe". I'm well aware of that, however.. things can get taken to extremes and research has shown that large amounts of Artificial Sweetner usage CAN disrupt GI function and can cause a lot of the symptoms mentioned in the video. Combine that with years and years of chronic overuse, and you can develop some issues. 

Also, while I won't be going through bags upon bags of stevia and Splenda every week (and I'll be abstaining from buying items such as sugar free jam, jello, etc), I'll still be drinking soda. As it's not something I consume in excess (Usually a glass for dinner every night). I'm confident in the fact that the things that have been consumed in excess are what need to be changed. (which diet soda isn't for me). There are also numerous studies in current existence stating that diet soda is perfectly "fine" in moderation. 

https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Gary_Marsh/publication/6011307_Aspartame_A_Safety_Evaluation_Based_on_Current_Use_Levels_Regulations_and_Toxicological_and_Epidemiological_Studies/links/0912f50bb9773d3e4f000000.pdf

As always, thanks for taking the time to watch the video!

title: ALL YOU CAN EAT SUSHI CHALLENGE! | 10,000+ CALORIES
description:
As I have a few contests coming up soon, I'm back at it with another capacity challenge! We visited an AYCE sushi restaurant located by me to test my skills! Each roll was definitely delicious, apart from the ones with avocado. All in all, estimated weight for everything was right around 12.5lbs which is great considering I consumed a decent amount of liquid during the challenge. Be sure to give the video a THUMBS UP if you haven't already and stay tuned for the next one!

title: LOW CALORIE TOP RAMEN SALAD | ELECTRIC EATS
description:
*Macros for this one will vary depending on the meat you use, if you use oil, etc. But this is by far one of my all time favorite salads to make if I’m training for a contest or just want something that’s going to FILL ME UP with less calories! Hope you guys enjoy it!*


Ingredient List: 
1 Head of Cabbage 
1/4 Cup White Vinegar 
1-2 tsp sugar
2 tablespoons soy sauce 
20g Top Ramen
Sesame Seeds 
Protein of your Choice 

Total Macros: 
~297 Calories 
~44g Carbs 
~5g Fat 
~20g Protein 
~2,533 mg Sodium 
~7g Fiber

title: WHAT DO MY FULL BODY WORKOUTS LOOK LIKE? | NEW CAMERA
description:
Just a sample “workout” that I’d do in the gym. Something simple that really only takes me 45 Minutes to an Hour. Here’s my typical routine down below! 


5-10 Minutes Mobility/Stretching 

Sumo Deadlifts (Or Conventional)
135lbs x 12 
185lbs x 8 
225lbs x 5 
275lbs x 5 
(working sets)
315lbs x 3
335lbs x 3 
345lbs x 3 (or top set at two or a single rep)

Squats (OR bench)
Bar x 12 
95lbs x 10
115lbs x 10
(working)
135lbs x 5 
145lbs x 5 
160lbs x 5 

Accessory Movement (Pyramid Sets)
DB Incline Bench 
35s x 12 
45s x 10
55s x 8
65s x 6 

BW Dips/Tricep Extensions 
5 sets (Pyramid)

Rack Pulls/GHRs 
5 Sets (Pyramid)

Cable Flies 
5 Sets (Pyramid)

title: MY FIRST "FULL DAY OF EATING"
description:
**GET AN ERIKTHEELECTRIC SHIRT HERE!**

**RECIPES USED!*

COCONUT GARLIC SHRIMP PASTA

SAUCE
5-6 sauteed garlic cloves 
1/2 Cup Coconut Milk
1 tsp Kosher Salt 

PASTA
2 Cups Pasta (any Kind) 
Tomatoes (Diced) 

Simply make the pasta like normal, add in diced tomato and set aside.
For the sauce, sauté the garlic cloves, put in food processor with coconut milk with kosher salt and process. 

Add in the sauce with the pasta and enjoy! 


PROTEIN GRANOLA! 

2 Cups Raw Oats 
1 Tablespoon Coconut Oil
3-4 Tablespoons Baking Coco 
1 Scoop Cellucor Whey 
Cinnamon 
Vanilla Extract (Optional)
1/4-1/2 Cup Coconut Sugar

title: THE McDONALD'S McMOUNTAIN CHALLENGE (World Record Attempt)
description:
(Check me out on social media!) 
► Instagram: http://bit.ly/2rWyjgU
► Facebook: http://bit.ly/2sXVR3t
► Twitter: http://bit.ly/2soQEog
► Snapchat: @ErikTheElectric 
► Strava: Erik”TheElectric”Lamkin
► GamerTag: ErikTheElectric

**ENOUGH ABOUT THE CLOCK COMMENTS!**
As is evidenced in my numerous live streams and vlogs, my clock on the wall in the back has been broken for the past 6 months. Up until a few days after this challenge was filmed, did I take it down. If you do not "believe" any of what is seen in this video, feel free to check out my numerous restaurant challenges and contest videos! 

This challenge was by far my biggest and most difficult EVER. I underestimated how much bread and starch would be involved in this challenge. But thankfully, I handle starches/carbs extremely well, and the music seemed to help! I have some BIG stuff coming up this summer and the next part of the year, so increasing my capacity is definitely on the game plan! 

Here’s what the “McMOUNTAIN” Consisted of..

80 Chicken MgNuggets 
2 Egg McMuffins
2 Sausage McMuffins (Cheese)
10 Hashbrowns
4 Large Fries 
4 Bacon McDoubles 
2 Filet O’ Fishes 
2 Normal Cheeseburgers
2 Fried Apple Pies 
8 Slices Cheddar Cheese
4 Ranch Packets
4 BBQ Packets
4 S&S Packets
Ketchup 
8 Pack of Hamburger Buns
8 Pack Potato Buns 
1 Bottle of Ranch

title: $1300 "LUCKY SEVEN CHICKEN CHALLENGE" | ErikTheElectric
description:
**CHALLENGE STARTS AROUND 4:05**

The "Lucky Seven Challenge" at China Blue in Corvallis, Oregon!

ONE HOUR.
7 POUNDS.
7 TYPES OF CHICKEN.
$1,300 JACKPOT.

What a hell of a challenge this was! Just a little bit of a backstory. This challenge features a progressive JACKPOT that increases every single month by $100 every time that it's not completed. This jackpot was won last year by Stephanie Wu who took home $1,500. I was a day away from booking a flight last year before I was informed that the challenge had been completed. Very discouraged, that being said.. When I was informed of the jackpot recently I vowed to take on the challenge. I headed out after class late on Wednesday night and took the 16 hour drive and the rest is history.


The challenge features SEVEN pounds of SEVEN different kinds of chicken.
Here they are, listed in order of the best tasting (in my opinion)

1. Hazelnut - 9/10 (Middle bowl)
2. Mandarin - 8/10
3. Sweet and Sour - 8/10
4. Orange - 7/10
5. General Taos- 7/10
6. Hunan - 5/10
7. Lemon - 3/10


Like I said, I went into this challenge extremely tired, fatigued and without much hunger as I drove 15 hours straight to get up to the restaurant. The chicken came out PIPING HOT. I used ice cubes and a separate plate to cool them down. The breading on the chicken was extra thick and I'd estimate the chicken weighed almost EIGHT pounds (instead of the listed 7 pounds). Since I do not consume meat, I was very nervous about taking down this colossal amount in one sitting. I finished the challenge around the 35 minute mark and took home the $1,300 check and got my picture on the wall!

title: The AYCE SUSHI CHALLENGE | 12,000+ Calories!
description:
DEFINITELY one of my tastiest challenges yet! (And with a $25 price tag for over $200 worth of sushi? I'm game!) Check out the video to see how I did! 

I do just want to say that I HATE Avocado (and Jalapenos). While every roll seemed to be loaded with both of them, I felt like the extremely large amounts of mayonnaise and cream cheese in most of the rolls masked the flavor of it, so I was able to handle it. It was more of the texture of the Avocado that started getting to me. The rolls were absolutely DELICIOUS, but after roll 15.. I started to feel the food wall. (Mainly because waiting over 20+ minutes for re-orders while the massive amounts of starch sat in my stomach really got to me as well). I'd estimate I took down between 9-10 lbs of sushi, and again... likely over $200 worth! So I ain't even mad!

title: FeedingTheElectric (14) White Sauce Vegan Pizza | Stress | Ethical Debate
description:
**FOR THE RECIPE!** 

Sauce: 
6 Whole Garlic Cloves 
¼ Cup Coconut Milk 
¼ tsp salt 
(Blend) 

Crust:
1.5 Cups Flour 
1 packet instant yeast 
1 tablespoon sugar 

Topping: 
Green Onion 
Cilantro 
Basil 
Garlic Powder 
Mrs. Dash Garlic Blend 



Start by mixing the yeast with 4 oz of warm water and sugar. Let stand for a few minutes and then add in your flour, let stand for 30-40 minutes util it rises. And then "pre bake" in the oven for 5-10 minutes. 

Top it with your sauce and additional toppings and bake for another 10-15 minutes and ENJOY! :)

title: The Great American BREAKFAST Challenge | 18,000+ Calories
description:
(Check me out on social media!) 
► Instagram: http://bit.ly/2rWyjgU
► Facebook: http://bit.ly/2sXVR3t
► Twitter: http://bit.ly/2soQEog
► Snapchat: @ErikTheElectric 
► Strava: Erik”TheElectric”Lamkin
► GamerTag: ErikTheElectric

This one was INSANE! As you guys may (or may not) know..Breakfast foods are my FAVORITE types of foods to eat! I wanted to create a “spin-off” of the original “Great American Diet Challenge”, but this time.. with ALL breakfast foods! I’ll admit, I overcooked the eggs, but other than that.. I think I did pretty well. Being that I do not eat meat and dairy regularly, this challenge was definitely a different one. But still enjoyable nonetheless, I’d estimate the total weight to be around 12-13 pounds! My capacity has DEFINITELY improved. 

The challenge consisted of..

6 Pack of Cinnabon Cinnamon Rolls 
1 Giant American “Breakfast Platter” which had..
An entire package of bacon
An entire package of Maple Sausage 
2 Lean Pockets 
12 eggs (Fried in coconut oil and topped with cheese)
An entire loaf of white bread with butter 
An entire pack of Kroger Hashbrowns
1 Box of Lucky Charms with An entire 2L of Cashew Milk
2 Packages of Vans Pancakes 
Half a jar of Peanut Butter with Chocolate Topping and Honey!


Like I said, it was an awesome challenge! Stay tuned for the next one!

description:
Just felt like many needed to be fully "aware" of the situation, since there's some obvious confusion floating about. I care deeply about each and every one of you that subscribe and have supported my channel ever since it's beginning. Without you guys (my subscribers) to encourage me and support my videos, I wouldn't be anything. 

That being said, If an opportunity presents itself and I have an opportunity to represent a company that..

1. I've used for years.
2. Know the products well enough and STAND behind them.
3. Am not being "pushed" to do or say anything (hence the reason why my reviews aren't "biased". 
4. Work with quality and genuine people.

I'm going to take that opportunity! 
Thanks for being awesome!

title: The Ultimate Waffles | Bears Game + Bike Ride | Happiness
description:
**Recipe for the waffles**

- 270g of Belgian Waffle Mix
- 2 Cups Almond/Cashew Milk
- 1/3 Cup Coconut Oil
- Chocolate Chips 
- Vanilla Extract 

1. Mix all above ingredients together
2. Preheat Waffle Iron
3. Pour onto Waffle Iron
4. Top with chocolate chips and syrup 
5. ENJOY!

description:
**CHECK OUT THE GLUCOSE NETWORK!**

So, I apologize if I offend(ed) anyone in this video. But, this is just the best decision for me right now. I hope you all can understand why I made the decision that I did. I thought about it quite a lot, and finally realized that this would be best for my physical AND mental health. 

Like I mentioned in the video, 99% of my "diet" consists of non-animal based sources anyways. Fruit, Oats, Sweet Potatoes, Rice, Lentils, Tofu, etc. I just feel that completely basing my life around my "diet" is just not the best way to live ones life.

title: MONDAY NIGHT MAYHEM #1 (Refeed) | ErikTheElectric
description:
**Bread Recipe**

- 4 Cups All Purpose Flour
- Salt
- 1 tsp Sugar
- 1 Packet of Yeast 

Simply take your flour, yeast, sugar, and salt and mix together with your water! Make sure you thoroughly incorporate it.

Let stand for ~30 minutes so that it can rise.

Bake in the oven at 385 degrees for around 20 minutes and ENJOY!



**Hummus Recipe**
- 1 Can Garbanzo Beans (Rinsed)
- 3 Tablespoons Olive Oil
- Garlic Powder
- Garlic Salt 
- Garlic Clove 

1. Take your can of beans and rinse/drain them
2. Put into magic bullet or food processor with 1/4 cup water and olive oil/spices.
3. Blend Throughly, and ENJOY!






This is going to be episode #1 in my weekly (or every other week) video series that I'm doing, dedicated to "refeeds". I feel that they're extremely beneficial to anyone that's moderately active looking to improve their performance. I'm definitely interested to see how far this takes me! 

Be sure to like, comment and subscribe for more!

title: End of Week 3 | Homemade PB | "Fishless" Crab Cakes!
description:
**BREAD RECIPE**

Ingredients:
- 1 Cup WW Flour 
- 1 Cup All Purpose Flour 
- 1 tsp Fast Acting Yeast
- Pinch of Salt
- Warm Water (To desired consistency) 
- 1 tsp Olive Oil 


1. Start by Pre-Heating the oven to 440 degrees F.
2. Take your flour and mix it in with your yeast.
3. Heat up 1-2 cups of warm water, and gradually add it in with the flour/yeast until you reach a "Doughy" consistency.
4. Cover your container with plastic wrap and let sit for 20-30 minutes until it's risen
5. Put into bread pan that's been sprayed nonstick cooking spray and bake in the oven for 25 minutes until golden brown.
6. ENJOY!

title: Homemade Calzone | Puffin Limited Edition Review | Front Squat PRs
description:
**RECIPE**
- 1 Cup WW Flour 
- 1 Cup White Flour
- 1 Pack Fast Rising Yeast
- Pinch of Sugar
- Garlic Salt 
- 1/4 Cup Warm water (depending on consistency) 
- Garlic Powder
- Mrs Dash
- Cheese 
- Pizza Sauce 

1. Start by heating up your water and preheating the oven to 425 degrees.
2. Next, put your flour in a bowl with yeast and dry ingredients. 
3. Add in water and mix with spatula/mixer
4. Mix throughly and cover with plastic wrap for 10-15 minutes
5. After 15 minutes pop onto a pizza dish and cover with pizza sauce and cheese (soy ftw) and put in the oven at 425 for 15 minutes
6. ENJOY!

title: Farrell's "Pigs Trough" 6 Scoop Sundae Qualifier! | ErikTheElectric
description:
So today, I took on the "pigs trough challenge" in order to to qualify for the "pro division" for Farell's Ice Cream 6th annual eating contest which will be held in downtown Brea, CA on the 19th of July!


At the finals m, the two individual who has the fastest qualifying time will go head to head with the reigning champ.. Naader Reda and the two will have to eat a 7lb sundae in the fastest time possible. The winner WILL RECEIVE $750 and free ice cream for an entire year! 

The record for today's 6 scoop sundae was 1:35 (which is when Naader did it back in 2013). I completed my sundae today in 1 minute and 8 seconds! 6 scoops of chocolate, strawberry, and vanilla! All topped with whipped cream and hot fudge! 


Let's hope my time holds up so that I can eat some more ice cream!

title: The 15,000 Calorie Peanut Butter Cup Cake | ErikTheElectric
description:
**Don't forget to hit that like/subscribe button for more challenges!**


(Also, feel free to follow my social media!)



Facebook: www.facebook.com/erikjameslamkin
Twitter: www.twitter.com/ErikTheElectric
Instagram: ErikTheElectric




And the latest challenge is LIVE. 
Me taking on a TEN...and a half pound peanut butter cup cake!
I gotta say, for throwing this thing together in only one hour (and just getting the idea to pop into my head only a few hours before hand. I'm pretty happy that I made it happen (despite the fact that the top COMPLETELY broke apart on me.. see the video for further clarification lol). 

This was BY FAR my most sweetest and most painful challenge yet.
The most I've ever done was 12.5lbs of protein/starchy carbs (soul food), so I wanted to recreate a volume/capacity challenge at home for my up coming challenge at a known restaurant. 

I used reeses pieces in the yellow cake batter and then reeses bites in the chocolate cake batter which made it come out nice and gooey (and delicious). Like I said, the top broke apart on me. Which made it pretty much impossible to frost the top. But I still managed to get the cake to come out and got it on the table. I finished around the 39 minute mark.


DEFINITELY a delicious challenge, but way too sweet! Next one will be savory for sure.


Be sure to give the video a watch and share it with your friends!

8 Minutes to down..

~1lb of Fries covered in chili cheese

I took this challenge with two other big eaters on Youtube. [B]Kevin Ross and Matt "Sweet-Tooth" Cohen[/B]. Never had met Kevin before... SUPER nice guy with a ton of talent when it comes to eating (The Same goes for Matt). Anyways, we had only 8 minutes to complete this challenge which was..

~2lbs of Beef smothered in cheese
~1lb of Fries covered in chili cheese 
~16oz Shake topped with one cherry


We both managed to DESTROY this one (but missed the record by 15 seconds). And kevin and I finished around 4:40. (We are still calling it a tie, even though I let kevin have the "win"). While this wasn't a full blown challenge with a ton of volume, I still had an AMAZING time with this one and had fun getting yet another win in my list of eating challenges..moving the number to TWENTY wins and ONE loss.

title: The "Cereal De Mayo" Challenge | 9,000 CALORIES
description:
**Don't forget to hit that like/subscribe button for more challenges!**


(Also, feel free to follow my social media!)



Facebook: www.facebook.com/erikjameslamkin
Twitter: www.twitter.com/ErikTheElectric
Instagram: ErikTheElectric




By far one of my most enjoyable challenges. I've been eating cereal since I popped out of the womb. I would literally down a box every morning for breakfast as a kid.. I've always laughed when people suggest serving sizes for cereal and have always said to myself "who in their right mind eats ONE SERVING" of cereal?". 


With this challenge, I wanted to go back to my childhood. Obviously, MANY of my old childhood favorite cereals have been discontinued (Oreo-Os, honey nut clusters, etc). But I picked ones that I enjoyed as a kid and still do! This challenge came in at 

~ 9 THOUSAND calories 
~ 1675 Grams of Carbohydrates
~ 145 Grams of Fat
~ 226 Grams of Protein 


The crazy amount of lactose got to me (as it always does in challenges that have milk, mainly because I NEVER drink milk and don’t do well with it). I thought about doing the challenge with almond milk, but it wouldn’t have been as “authentic” in my opinion. 


Like I said, pretty fun and enjoyable. My last challenge was almost a month ago so I wanted to get back into the swing of things.


STAY TUNED FOR THE NEXT ONE!

Well this was certainly my “coldest” challenge yet. I received a message a little over a week ago from “The Storm” on YouTube inquiring about doing a “challenge” together. It was simple and straight forward. To create the most epic sundae/banana split ever.
A one gallon tub of ice cream (I was only able to find 1.25 gallons), bananas, cherries, and whipped cream. I went out and found some “better” options not just because I’m a HUGE reeses peanut butter cup fan, but because I wanted a little more variety in this one.

I gave myself 30 minutes to complete this 8 POUND challenge. 
I finished around the 21 mark after a TON of brain freeze and a huge sugar rush. 
This was my first ice cream challenge yet, and by FAR the most enjoyable.

title: ErikTheElectric's MLE Debut | Knott's Pie Eating Contest 2015
description:
**Don't forget to hit that like/subscribe button for more challenges!**


(Also, feel free to follow my social media!)



Facebook: www.facebook.com/erikjameslamkin
Twitter: www.twitter.com/ErikTheElectric
Instagram: ErikTheElectric

An AMAZING experience was had today. 

As many of you know, this was my first ever Major League Eating contest! This was the Boysenberry Pie Eating Contest at a place called Knott’s Berry Farm in Buena Park, CA. I came into this with only one prior contest under my belt, and little to know speed-eating skills. I cannot help but be extremely disappointed in my performance, but in the grand scheme of things.. I was on stage with the top eaters in the world and was only a few pounds away from them. So, I still see a glimmer of hope on the horizon. 

I’m no “speed eater” and my speciality lies more in capacity based challenges, so I knew that this contest was going to be a true test to my skills. I had NEVER in my life had boysenberry pie, prior to this contest (which came back to bite me in the ass). The pie was EXTREMELY sour and “tart”, which are my least favorite “tastes” when it comes to eating.  More notably, the pies were literally nothing but “goo” with little to no crust whatsoever. Which perplexed me because of the “debris rule”, essentially you are supposed to eat your pies with little to no debris left behind in order to move onto the next plate of pie. Which is where I was stumped, because regardless of how thorough I was with the pie it was literally so messy that no matter what.. there would still be debris on the plate. I realized this right off the bat, and thought nothing of it.. as far as I could see, eating 90-95% of the plate should be substantial enough.  So I worked my way up to 5,6,7, and then eventually finished with 10lbs as my total (or so I thought). 

As you’ll see in the end of the video, the judge (Sam) came up with a number that he thought was “best” and decided to knock 1.5lbs off of my total. (Nothing against him, he was just using his judgment). However, when it came down to it, I was placed 6th out of 12 people. The person that placed 5th, finished with 9lbs. In my eyes, I realistically placed 3rd or 4th. It’s unfortunate, but as I said this was DEFINITELY a learning experience for me. And taught me a lot about not only competitive eating, but the world of competitive eating and what to do and what NOT to do. 

I’m trying my hardest not to be discouraged, but at this point I can’t help but wonder if this is really “for me”. This could be my first (and last) challenge. I DID drown my sorrows in some fried chicken and biscuits afterwards though! Which was awesome!


STAY TUNED FOR MORE CHALLENGES COMING SOON!

Man that was rough..

Really was stoked to do my FIRST EVER food challenge at home! I was originally going to try/attempt to topple matt stonies current Chicken Mg nugget record (120). But I really thought about it, and figured I wouldn’t really enjoy that sort of challenge.. what’s one thing I’ve really always loved? PIE! And it made perfect sense, because I have my first ever MLE competition coming up in just over a week! And what better time to practice then today? 

I ended up picking up two claim jumper pies (not the best), one store bout pumpkin pie, and one entire family sized pack of chicken pot pies. ALL OF THESE PIES COMBINED WEIGHED JUST OVER 8.5 POUNDS. That’s over 10,500 calories, 595g Fat, 1,152g carbs, 170g protein (lol), and 10,500mg of sodium. Pretty nuts! The amount of sugar in the peanut butter pie was so painful, peanut butter is by far one of my favorite things in this entire world to eat. But each spoonful was an overload, it was gnarly. 

I would say that the best part about this challenge was the dutch apple pie with the crumble topping. It was a pain to have to thaw everything out and then bake it, but I got it plated up and going when I could! I started feeling the pain about 15 minutes in, and that’s when the sugar rush started hitting me. My biggest mistake was saving the peanut butter pie for LAST instead of tackling it first. It was undoubtedly the most dense and most rich pie. 

This was tough, but VERY good training. I was able to get everything down in 64 minutes (just over an hour). NOW it’s time for next week!

title: Crushing All Carbs (#2): IHOP, 7,000 Calories, Weigh in, Deadlifts!
description:
Started the month off STRONG with this one! 


**FOLLOW MY SOCIAL MEDIA!**

FB: www.facebook.com/erikjameslamkin
IG: ErikTheElectric
Twitter: ErikTheElectric 






So today was the first "official" day of my new self experiment. Just going to be hammering down carbs for the remainder of the month and see where things stand. I've been feeling AMAZING lately (both physically and mentally) but I'm wondering if things can get even better. I'm not sure if I made the point yet already, but I'm also doing this self experiment to see how much strength I can gain WHILE cycling AND getting back into resistance training again. It's a common misconception that the two simply cannot go hand in hand. But I really can't subscribe to that idea quite yet. 


---
I started off today super motivated, and hungry for the day! I weighed in today at 164.8 lbs (post ride) and will not be weighing in for the month. (Just wanted to get a starting weight). Today was my only day off for the week, so I wanted to get a nice relaxing ride in.. And ended up flooring it today! I managed to make it ~80 miles with an average speed at around 17mph (which is pretty decent, but still a little slow). I had quite a bit of time to ride today and it was nice to get out and do some climbing for the first portion of the ride and then finish it off with some distance. 
I managed to make it up north, and then turn around and let the tailwind lead me back into my town. 


After my ride, I decided to indulge in a craving and hit up IHOP for a post ride (and pre training) snack! 
Decided to go with the new strawberry rhubarb croissant, hash browns/egg whites and ham/ with a stack of pancakes. Oddly enough, this meal made me feel like absolute trash afterwards (while I was hungry only 30 minutes afterward. Most likely was the cream cheese in the croissant (as I do not handle dairy well AT ALL) but regardless I still got in the gym and trained as intense as I could for 45 minutes. (Before heading home to the girlfriend) 


---
Training actually went pretty well tonight! 
Granted my deadlifts are STILL at a standstill (365x3) and I ended up busting open my shins and bleeding on the bar. I wasn't expecting any PRs, ESPECIALLY after the ride today (climbing yesterday) and with the fact that I've been out of the gym for 2 weeks. Will be working my way back up to four plates, and the progressive overload will be gradual but it WILL happen. I will not stop until I get my strength back.

title: ErikTheElectric vs The B.O.B (12.5lbs of Food)
description:
Check out Island Soul Bistro here!

http://www.island-soul-bistro.com


**FOLLOW ME FOR MORE CHALLENGES!**

IG: ErikTheElectric
FB: www.facebook.com/erikjameslamkin
Twitter: ErikTheElectric








WITHOUT A DOUBT
My biggest and hardest challenge yet. Last night, I attempted to take down the “B.O.B” platter at “Island Soul Bistro” in Lemon Grove, CA. This was their first EVER food challenge, so I was VERY excited to take this thing on. And then I went into the back kitchen and saw it being plated/made.. This thing was TWELVE and a half pounds of straight up soul food! An entire family sized platter called the “Best of Both Worlds” platter, red velvet chicken and waffles, and peach cobbler to top it all off! 

Before I say anything else, I just want to mention how friendly and awesome the ENTIRE staff was and how awesome it was to get the CRAZY amount of support that I had with the challenge. At least FIFTY people came out just to see the challenge take place at the restaurant and it was without a doubt my favorite challenge!

I started off with the protein (obviously) and worked my way through the ribs. They were tough, but I got through them. Each bone felt like it was a mini baseball bat, but I got through them in around 4-5 minutes. After that I worked through the chicken (very tough) and fish and then started with the sides. Each side felt like PURE death as everything was a heavy.. and I mean HEAVY starch.“Potatoes.. Rice.. Greens.. Beans.. Mac and Cheese, and then a few pounds of battered chicken and waffles after that?” I questioned myself as I finished the meats, I didn’t know if I really had it in me. After all of my challenges, this was the only time I where I really questioned it and my ability. But then the infamous “Second wind” hit me, and I powered through the collard greens, beans, chicken and rice (my favorite), mac and cheese, pickled dish, and then the potatoes to finish it off. The red velvet chicken and waffles (by this point) were EXTREMELY tough to get down and each waffle was like a brick in my stomach. The chicken was tough, the waffles were dry (since they had been out for that period of time, but STILL delicious). But I kept going and going regardless of the signals my stomach was sending to me. Finally I got all of them down...

”Oh, you thought it was over?
The head chef brought out my “dessert” to top it all off.. Peach Cobbler. And I shook my head in awe as I looked at it being set down on the table. Oddly enough this was one of my favorite parts of the entire meal! It was smooth, creamy and delicious! 
As I shoveled the last bite of ice cream into my mouth, I FINISHED THE 12.4 POUNDS OF FOOD IN 35 MINUTES! Setting the mark as the FIRST EVER PERSON TO EVER ACCOMPLISH IT! So stoked, but so painful. After completing this challenge, this solidified (to me) that I need to really start taking my challenges to the next level.. 

EXPECT SOMETHING BIG IN THE NEAR FUTURE!

title: Fuddruckers 4lb "Fat Tuesday" Burger/Fry Challenge!
description:
**Follow For MORE Challenges** (Just hit that subscribe button!)




IG: ErikTheElectric
FB: www.facebook.com/erikjameslamkin
Twitter: ErikTheElectric



**RANDYS CHANNEL**

https://www.youtube.com/user/RandySantel/featured

WEBSITE

http://www.foodchallenges.com/




BOOM! 


Another eating challenge completed! I had tons of fun with this one. This was a very enjoyable challenge and was done at Fuddruckersrestaurant. I had one hour to eat a 3 pound burger (which was turkey) and also had to eat one pound of sweet potato fries. I met up with a friend from the boards organ Panthers a.k.a. Josh. Josh took on this challenge for your ago and finished at 34 minutes so he wanted to show up as last timeand beat his time. This is my first time attending the challenge so I had no idea what to expect. Josh started out a little bit ahead of me, I ended up starting around two minutes I had of Josh. UnfortunatelyThe burgers were already made before we came in were a bit cold when brought out in the sweet tater fries were soggy. However, the burger was very delicious and moist. Before this challenge I hadn't had a turkey burger in years! 

We both started off strong I'd swing about this like normal the challenge itself wasn't that substantial 4 pounds of food is it really that much in the grand scheme of things. Burger challenge is usually consist of a huge line with a huge Patty but surprisingly the Patty wasn't that huge. I was able to get the party down in the in only four or fiveminutes. After that I work the top on and had everything down and completed at around a 10 minute mark. Josh ended up DESTROYING his old time with a completed time of 15 minutes and 35 seconds! 

I ended up finishing my burger at 14 minutes and 33 seconds! WHICH IS A NEW RECORD TIME!  I put the fries down pretty quickly and was able to win the challenge and get my gift certificate for $25 (Josh gave me his so thanks josh!). This challenge really wasn't challenging at ALL, I actually wanted to do TWO! But didn't want to pay the 40$. I've always loved Fuddruckers in with her all the time as a kid, and I'll be back for more. The manager is actually really cool and told us all about the history of the challenge and told us that he talk to corporate about setting up a two burger challenge specifically for me when they do it next time Labor Day. I'll definitely be coming back the next time to do the challenge. I ended up getting my gift cards and buying more food to bring home! Gotta love cookies, brownies, rice crispy treats and cinnamon rolls... Right?!

title: The "Teds Tater Tot Challenge" (5lbs of Tots + Cheese-Steak)
description:
Instagram: ErikTheElectric
FB: www.facebook.com/ErikTheElectric
Twitter: ErikTheElectric




The Location:
“Players Bar and Grill”, San Marcos, CA



The Challenge:


5 Pounds of “Sloppy Tater tots”, creamy cheddar cheese, chili, Philly Cheesesteak meat. Topped with sour cream and 2 fried eggs. 30 minutes to finish, or I had to fork over 35$!

.



The prize:


Name up on the wall of fame

Meal free

T shirt

Eternal Glory!











Final Thoughts:


So tonight I took on Players Sports Bar’s “Teds Tot Challenge”. 5 pounds of delicious, cheese filled goodness! The funny and most notable part about this challenge is that it’s RIGHT ACROSS THE STREET FROM MY HOUSE! I’ve been searching around San Diego for remaining food challenges and was made aware of this only a few days ago, so I just HAD to go and take it down!



Only ONE person has done this before, he managed to finish it in 29 minutes...You have 30 minutes to finish the challenge. So I wanted to enjoy it, but not go too hard too fast. The plate/food were weighed and it came out piping hot, I could tell that I was going to be able to take it down.. it was just a matter of what time it would be done.



The challenge was simple, I actually had a few of my girlfriends fries during the challenge. The cheese was HEAVY and disgusting, seriously though.. I had to put ketchup and ranch on most of the tots for it to actually be somewhat appealing. After I got bored of that, I ordered a sprite just to switch up the flavor profiles.. but I gutted through it and got it done. In 18 minutes I had this bad boy down! I wasn’t going for speed, but I’m sure if I was.. it would be done in under 12-15 minutes. The best part about the challenge was the meat, it was cooked perfectly! The nastiest part of it was (of course) the massive amount of cheese and chili. But I still enjoyed it nonetheless!

The roll itself tasted AMAZING, the cream cheese and the salmon were KILLER on every level possible.. and the spicy mayo on top..  SEALED THE DEAL!  I was able to put the monster down, get the entire meal free (who DOESN’T like free sushi?) and get my name up on the wall of fame! The first ever winner at the location! 

For my first sushi challenge, I can definitely say I’m proud of what I accomplished.

title: "The Day of Glory" (25,000 Calorie Cheat Day)
description:
**FOLLOW ME FOR MORE CHALLENGES!**

Facebook: www.facebook.com/erikjameslamkin
Instagram: erikjameslamkin
Twitter: ErikTheElectric




Well, this was by far the DUMBEST idea I've ever had for a food challenge.. but.. I DID IT! 25,000 calories, all taken down in the span of ~12-13 hours. Quite honestly, I'd NEVER suggest to eat anywhere near this amount to anyone. I've never felt more sick in my entire life after countless eating challenges. To be a little bit more clear though, I personally believe it was doing the "broken yolk challenge" as my first meal..that set me up for the majority of the pain during the day.. as I trained AFTER that. Which was what made me feel like I was almost on the verge of death. Try doing cardio, heavy squats, deadlifting, and benching after consuming 7 pounds of food and almost 25,000mg of sodium. Yeah, not too enjoyable... Heh. The broken yolk challenge itself was pretty fun, I was NOT going for time as I wanted to enjoy myself and pace myself because I knew that I had to take down A LOT of food afterwards. I managed to do it in 50 minutes, got the meal free and walked out! 

I did my BEST to try to minimize cost as much as possible with this challenge. Other than having to pay for all of the gatorades, the candy, the KFC and Panda Express and the ingredients for the "Ultimate Cookie" I would say that I did pretty well! All in all, the 25,000 calorie day (well, 15,000 calories of it was what I REALLY had to pay for) cost me around 65$ total.. which wasn't too shabby!

My favorite part of the day was by FAR my "Home-made Peanut Butter Butterfinger Cookie" which was LOADED with deliciousness and beats the hell out of ANY cake, pie, or dessert concoction out there! The recipe and ingredients were SUPER simple:
Ingredients:


    1.50 cup, All-purpose Flour
    0.75 cup(s), Kroger
    0.75 cup(s), White Granulated
    50.00 g (1 egg), Egg
    2.00 Tbsp, Peanut Butter Baking Chips

    2.00 TBSP, Milk Chocolate Chips
    1.00 tsp, Pure Vanilla Extract
    50.00 g (2Tbsp), Creamy Peanut Butter.
    0.50 cup, Butter - Salted






All in all, this was a pretty fun challenge. I got the idea after watching "Beastaesthetics" and "RZ fitness" try it on youtube and wanted to see how much I could take down! 
Stay tuned for the next one!

title: Conquering the Climb: Palomar Mountain
description:
So today, I did something I've been wanting to do for YEARS! Ever since I started cycling, and have been in the cycling community here in Southern California. EVERYONE has always talked about "Palomar Mountain" (the tallest climb IN San Diego) as being the game changer for riders who think they can climb! I can't tell you how many people who've asked me "Why haven't you done Palomar yet?"

No answer really. It's honestly been so intimidating just thinking about that damn monster mountain, I've heard horror stories of guys crashing bikes to their deaths, people getting hit, people bonking midway up the mountain, etc. So today, I got my baby out and rose from San Marcos to Palma Valley and went balls to the wall, gave it everything I had.. And I MADE IT TO THE TOP! My VERY FIRST TIME! Granted, I hit every possible headwind, ripped my headphones in half, and felt like a drone afterwards but I told myself, "You're not stopping UNTIL YOU GET TO THE TOP". No matter what I did, my legs kept moving, my mind kept set on the goal I set for myself and I made my way to my destination and to the top of that damn mountain. 

Today was a true test to my riding ability. I feel like it's only human nature to underestimate our potential, especially at the things that WE LOVE. But when you accomplish goals, and achieve unexpected things it only motivates you to keep pushing harder. And to NEVER QUIT doing what you love, to strive to better yourself.. Day after day! 


LETS DO IT AGAIN! 
(Next stop, Mount Everest!)

description:
**Feel Free to Check out my other Eating Challenges on my Channel!**

Like, Comment, and Subscribe! 


IG: erikjameslamkin
Facebook: www.facebook.com/erikjameslamkin
Twitter: ErikTheElectric









Well! I DID IT!
15,000 calories.
No Liquid Calories. All Food. 


Honestly, I’m glad I did this “cheat day” challenge first.. as opposed to doing the 10,000 calorie “completely clean” challenge (essentially consuming 10,000 calories with completely “clean food”). This one was actually pretty great, I think the only downside to this one was how much everything cost! (Although I did have a gift card to Coldstone and Sonic which was definitely good). 

The challenge itself wasn’t necessarily “difficult”, I definitely knew that the guys on YouTube complaining about feeling deathly full after their infamous “10k challenges” were just complaining, lmao. I wanted to simply see how much food I could put down in a single DAY (well.. to be honest it was basically half a day, as I started eating at around 11:45 a.m and finished a bit after midnight). I definitely surprised the hell out of myself and found myself just over 15,000 calories for the entire day. 

The other downside to the challenge was proper planning and the fact that I feel like I could’ve gotten better filming angles/pictures. Unfortunately, we had company over during the day and I didn’t want to be filming myself eating a bunch of food at our table. At the same time, I wasn’t going to be taking my camera into Costco and out with us. (Hence the reason why a lot of angles are shot from my iPhone). 

Overall I’m pretty happy with the result and how good I did! (Other than a HUGE stomach, a ton of bloating, and some nausea)

title: ErikTheElectric takes on Oink and Moo's "Triple Headed Monster" Burger Challenge!
description:
The "Triple Headed Monster Burger Challenge" 
(Now called the "LAMKINATOR")

I had 47.5 minutes to finish the Goliath burger. Only ONE person has ever finished the burger in the entire history or the restaurant. Even Jamie "The Bear" McDonald was unable to take the best down when he came into the restaurant a while back! (If you look closely on The Wall of Shame, you can see his picture). If I finished the burger, I received it FREE OF CHARGE, eternal glory, I got to name the burger after myself, AND I got my name up on the wall of fame! I ALSO got to add in "my layer" of whatever I wanted for the next challenger to try and defeat! 

The burger came out and I was blown away...
- 4 sets of buns 
- 8 patties (4 habanero patties.. SO spicy) 
- 1 whole pulled pork sandwich
- 1 Mac and cheese fritter on top 
- 5 fried eggs 
- Onion Rings 
- mountain of lettuce/tomato/onion 
- 2 pickles 
- 12 slices of bacon 
- 12 slices of cheese 
- One whole Kielbasa Sausage 
- 21 oz soft drink (must be finished) 
- 2 POUNDS of waffle fries 
(Well over 7 pounds of food) 





This was easily my most difficult challenge, but definitely delicious and worth it! The previous winner "Arturo" designed the burger to be "unbeatable" with the habanero patties AND the pulled pork sandwich at the top. As soon as the burger came out and I started, I made sure to work my way down and get the burger down FIRST. THIS WAS MY FIRST EVER CHALLENGE WITH SODA! (I chose sprite) to my surprise, it actually helped me quite a bit! I talked to a friend of mine before hand (Randy Santell) and the restaurant is notorious for adding MORE to the burger than what is listed, again.. I was surprised to find 2 additional sets of buns, more fries and more vegetables than what I saw in the previous pictures. But, I just kept eating!


I made sure to pace myself and keep working the burger until I finished it. Once the meat and vegetables were done, it was time for the bread (which I dipped in ranch). After that was painfully over, all that was left was the fries! These were absolutely disgusting, cold and soggy. I was able to power through them and finish at 41 minutes and become the NEW RECORD HOLDER FOR THE BURGER! I chose to "leave my mark" for the next challenger by choosing to put a HALF CHICKEN ontop of the burger for the next person who attempts to take down the beast! 

IT IS NOW NAMED AFTER ME! 
I was going to go with the "electrifyer", but chose "The LAMKINATOR" instead! (My last name fit better) 
I got my money back, got DESSERT, and my name up on the wall of fame! 
Again, this was easily the most difficult challenge I've ever done. But I can finally say, after doing this.. And talking with the designer of the burger, I WILL be looking into the MLE and will be doing a pro eating qualifier soon! 


I CANT WAIT!

title: ErikTheElectric Takes on Citizen's Grill and Bar's "24 Slider Challenge!"
description:
**VISIT AND SUPPORT! **

http://www.foodchallenges.com/

For everything related to eating big, eat feats, and for eating strategies!



HUGE shoutout to..Randy Santel for all of the support! And to everyone else! 


Let me just start by saying this was by FAR my hardest challenge yet..
I came into this challenge knowing that the BREAD would be tough.. and oh it was! I watched “Furious Pete’s” video this morning of himself taking down the challenge in 19 minutes flat.. and I wanted to beat that. Unfortuantely, I wasn’t able to beat his time due to not preparing properly and after a night of light drinking. 
After seeing pete struggle with this challenge on video this morning, I contemplated even doing it.. but I figured I was IN LAS VEGAS! It was time to do something epic, and “push my limits”. 

The bread came out hard and VERY tough. It was WAY too doughy and thick and was like eating wall plaster. The patties were the opposite, absolutely delicious and perfectly cooked. On the other hand, EACH slider came with an obsene amount of pickles and onions.. (which I despise). The HARDEST part of the challenge was having to do ALL of this in ONLY 24 minutes (as I am NOT a speed eater). 

Proud to say that I powered through, and I managed to end up being the FIFTH person to ever complete the challenge out of dozens! Time was just shy of 23 minutes! And I earned my way up on the wall of fame! . Again, this was my hardest challenge I’ve ever done. I’d estimate that it was between 5-6lbs of food.. within a 24 minute period! Other than the time limit, I definitely think I could’ve done it quicker if I had paced myself at the beginning I took down WAY too much bread, way too fast at the start of the challenge. Which filled me up very quickly! 


Looking forward to the next one!

title: ErikTheElectric takes on Nikky Rottens "Ultimate Burger Challenge"
description:
** FAST FORWARDING STARTS @ 7:20 **



You have one hour to clean your plate. If you finish in 30 minutes, we’ll buy it for you! This friggin’ burger weighs in at 2 ½ pounds leaving grown men crying for mercy! 2lbs of Brandt beef, American Cheese, Lettuce, tomato, onion AND Rotten Sauce on a custom super-sized bun with fries on the side (1.5 lbs). No substitutions! Don’t even ask! 


So.. Tonight I decided to attempt the “baddest”  burger challenge in San Diego (and the biggest). This was my official “coming out of retirement” food challenge. This was my [u] FIRST ever “burger challenge”.. and after how tonight went, it certainly won’t be my last! [/u] I woke up this morning,  and after some researching.. figured I’d go about this burger challenge.  This challenge has been on my radar ever since the day after my last challenge (the 35 pancake IHOP challenge), so I figured I’d do it today. 

The waiter told me that he had never seen anyone actually finish the burger before, but the manager personally told me that the record time was “22 minutes and 30 seconds”. So, after hearing that.. my desire to simply beat the 30 minute time limit and get the meal free.. turned into wanting to beat the all time record. I decided to change my technique for this one and I [u] went STRAIGHT for the protein.. the 2.5lb patty[/u]. It was honestly delicious and perfect temeperature.. (I made the mistake of not letting the 12 lb sandwich I attempted not cool off before eating it and it filled me up from the steam [/u] I got the meat down relatively quickly, and then went straight for the bun! The hostess told me that the bun was literally like “eating an entire load of bread”, and from the size.. it was actually bigger than my entire head. Quite honestly, the top was like hell.. it was buttered/toasted.. and went down hard, the bottom was easy (as it was soggy). 

Next were the fries.. the sweet potato fries were absolutely delicious. I wouldn’t have been able to get through it (well, I would’ve but not like I did.) without the syrup, ranch, and amazing BBQ sauce that they had on hand. I decided to eat those, (and the rest of the bun) last. The veggies (tomatoes, lettuce, and pickle) were randomly eaten. 

Overall, this was probably my most enjoyable challenge I’ve ever done. I’ve always wanted to do this, and had heard great things about it. I was ORGINALLY going to do simply a 2lb burger challenge today.. but decided to go for the biggest, and baddest in San Diego. And after taking down that entire thing (4+lbs worth.. the 2.5lb patty + the bun + the 1.5lb fries) I’m VERY confident that I’ll be making my way back into doing eating challenges again! I can’t wait for my next one!

title: Cellucor's "Red Velvet Cake Batter" Protein Powder Review
description:
Overview: 9/10
The moment that I saw Cellucor announce this flavor, I knew I was going to get it. "Red Velvet Cake Batter" is among Cellucors new line of flavors that came out at the start of the new year. I ordered mine right when body building.com started stocking it in their online store, and I'm so glad that I did. My last experience was with their "Cor Fetti" flavor which I loved as well. 


[URL=http://s1276.photobucket.com/user/Eriktheelectric/media/D76C2F11-5829-4F43-9C6A-6754A376E0EB_zpsjctzltay.jpg.html][IMG]http://i1276.photobucket.com/albums/y461/Eriktheelectric/D76C2F11-5829-4F43-9C6A-6754A376E0EB_zpsjctzltay.jpg[/IMG][/URL]

--------



Taste: 7/10
When I first tested and tasted Cellucor's last flavor, "Cor Fetti Cake Batter" I had found my new favorite flavor from Cellucor (it beat out cinnamon swirl as my new favorite). To be honest, I expected the same to happen with this flavor since I LOVE red velvet cupcakes and red velvet cake. My first impression when I first broke open the tub and got a whiff of the powder brought me back to last summer when I had the time of my life for my sisters birthday and we had real, authentic red velvet cupcakes...
[URL=http://s1276.photobucket.com/user/Eriktheelectric/media/cake_zpsff8910aa.jpg.html][IMG]http://i1276.photobucket.com/albums/y461/Eriktheelectric/cake_zpsff8910aa.jpg[/IMG][/URL]
[URL=http://s1276.photobucket.com/user/Eriktheelectric/media/null_zps9ba0190e.jpg.html][IMG]http://i1276.photobucket.com/albums/y461/Eriktheelectric/null_zps9ba0190e.jpg[/IMG][/URL]


----

Nutrition: 9/10
Always good with Cellucor. The macros and calories really cannot be beat here. 120 kcals and low fat/low carb, there really isn't anything better to be honest. Cellucor still manages to put out amazing flavors while catering to low calorie dieters or anyone looking for a delicious tasting protein, even on a calorie restricting diet.
Quite personally, I've had to bump my protein needs up to 280g-300g a day. So I've come to realize that I need much more of this ontop of my daily whole food/foods take. And when you have delicious protein like Red Velvet Cake Batter at your disposal.. it makes things not only easier, but so much more delicious!

----


Versatility: 10/10
This was honestly the biggest surprise to me. I've ALWAYS had trouble with past proteins. Whether it be mixing them with oatmeal, making them with recipes, sludges, etc. THIS IS THE MOST VERSATILE FLAVOR THAT I'VE EVER WORKED WITH! And coming from someone who's used dozens of other protein brands in my kitchen, that's saying something. My first creation was a protein loaf and it couldn't have gone better and couldn't have TASTED better. 

Some Creations:
Red Velvet Protein Loaf
[URL=http://s1276.photobucket.com/user/Eriktheelectric/media/8F6C8E92-BC43-4E1D-914F-FF47A8FCA44A_zpsox2pu3jt.jpg.html][IMG]http://i1276.photobucket.com/albums/y461/Eriktheelectric/8F6C8E92-BC43-4E1D-914F-FF47A8FCA44A_zpsox2pu3jt.jpg[/IMG][/URL]

Protein Oatmeal (AKA Pro-Oats)
[URL=http://s1276.photobucket.com/user/Eriktheelectric/media/4BFF8F2B-5614-4AEE-AE97-432C0FAACA85_zpslzo6gjd9.jpg.html][IMG]http://i1276.photobucket.com/albums/y461/Eriktheelectric/4BFF8F2B-5614-4AEE-AE97-432C0FAACA85_zpslzo6gjd9.jpg[/IMG][/URL]


Basic Sludge 
[URL=http://s1276.photobucket.com/user/Eriktheelectric/media/49BF7653-5777-4117-BCB8-1D4906493356_zps9wgi5mre.jpg.html][IMG]http://i1276.photobucket.com/albums/y461/Eriktheelectric/49BF7653-5777-4117-BCB8-1D4906493356_zps9wgi5mre.jpg[/IMG][/URL]


—

I wish there was more for me to say, you cannot go wrong with this flavor! While it definitely isn't as good as Cor - Fetti, you will not be disappointed with Cellucor's new flavor "Red Velvet Cake Batter".

title: No bake Oatmeal Protein Bars
description:
Protein Bars

Ingredients:
100g of Oats
1 Scoop Cellucor Whey
½ Cup Greek Yogurt
2 Table Spoons (1 serving) Fat Free Cream Cheese
¼ Cup Stevia 
2 Servings liquid egg whites 
2 tablespoons coco powder


Directions:
Start by taking a cookie sheet, line it with foil, and spray it down with PAM.

Next, take your cream cheese, sweetener and egg whites and yogurt and mix them thoroughly in a mixing bowl.

Next, add in your oats and stevia, protein powder, coco powder and incorporate thoroughly.

Finally add the mixture onto your baking dish and spread out evenly. 

Freeze for 1-2 hours and cut into however many bars you desire! 

Enjoy!


Macros (for entire tray):
627 Calories
9g of Fat
86g Carbohydrate
54g of Protein 
12g of Fiber

Macros (Cut into 6 bars):
104 Calories
1.5g of Fat
14g Carbohydrates
9g of Protein
2g of Fiber

title: ErikTheElectric takes on 35 IHOP Pancakes!
description:
Final Thoughts:
This challenge was pretty enjoyable, but a hard one. Eating 8lbs of pancakes (35 pancakes), straight starch is pretty difficult. I most likely could've made it to 40+ pancakes, but I had a pretty big meal only a few hours prior and just simply walked in and took on the challenge. 

I would say the most frustrating part of the challenge was having to wait and reorder pancakes in between eating them. The waiter would come around every 5-10 minutes, and I had to keep asking for more because she simply didn't believe that I could keep eating more. That being said you could ONLY order TWO PANCAKES MAXIMUM at one time. I started at 5.. but that's as much as they could give me.. Pretty stupid rule in my opinion.

I just got off the phone with the manager of the IHOP I went too, and they said that they would be giving me free meals and are "definitely sure" I'll be representing their restaurant in this years "IHOP pancake bowl" so I'm pretty happy with my performance. 

Waking up today though, I've never felt this bad after a challenge haha. My lower back is killing me, and I'm still hot/shaky from eating all of that sugar and starch. I've been constantly thirsty and have been downing water like no tomorrow. 

Pancake bowl, here we come!

title: ErikTheElectric takes on Shakespeares Pub and Grill's  "Great White Whale Food Challenge"
description:
The Location:
Shakespeare's pub and grill in San Diego, CA. 

The Challenge:
Finish a platter of their signature Fish & Chips -- containing a 2Lb piece of battered Cod, 2Lb of chips and a side of peas in 45 minutes or less.

[URL=http://s1276.photobucket.com/user/Eriktheelectric/media/Great%20White/ScreenShot2014-01-02at92620PM_zpsdb2ca68c.png.html][IMG]http://i1276.photobucket.com/albums/y461/Eriktheelectric/Great%20White/ScreenShot2014-01-02at92620PM_zpsdb2ca68c.png[/IMG][/URL]

The prize: 
Eternal Glory, The 25$ meal is free, and the "I finished the Great White Whale Challenge" T shirt. 


Final Thoughts:
Enjoyed the heck out of this one guys. Honestly, I've never had fried fish that's tasted this good. I'm actually still hungry as I type this..The batter was perfect and crispy. Unfortunately, it came out EXTREMELY hot and it was a bit hard to eat initially, but I worked my way through it pretty well. Overall, the best part of the meal/challenge was the dipping the fish/fries in their home-made tarter sauce. It was absolutely delicious. 

I knew coming into this challenge that I was going to beat it pretty easily. 5lbs of food really isn't that much to me. I considered this challenge an "appetizer" to my coming food challenges in 2014. I took my time with this one and chatted with my friends that went along with me. (All of them got fish and chips as well, the place is known for that. 

The fries got pretty boring and bland after 10 minutes (they began to get soggy), but I enjoyed them. I would say the worst part of the challenge was eating the bowl of peas (I can't stand peas). So I doused them in ketchup and wolfed them down. (like I did with the fries). 

Overall guys, I'm stoked about this challenge and even MORE excited for the future and the coming challenges in 2014!

title: Eriks Cauliflower Pizza!
description:
Ingredients: 
2 eggs 
2 Cups Raw Cauliflower
½ Cup Cheese (of your choice)
½ Cup Stewed Tomatoes
Mrs. Dash
Garlic Sault
Any other additional toppings

Directions: 
Start by preheating your oven to 350 degrees.
Next, spray down your baking tray with non stick cooking spray.

Next take your Raw cauliflower and place it in a food processor or blender, and process thoroughly until you get a "rice" like consistency. Next, place your rice cauliflower in a bowl with your two eggs, mix together with your 2 tablespoons of yogurt, and ¼ cup of cheese. Finally, take your mixture and put it onto of your baking dish and bake at 375 degrees for 20-25 minutes, until you get your "crust".

Finally take it out, add on your tomatoes and additional ¼ cup of cheese and bake again until your cheese melts and ENJOY!


Macros (without topping):
352 kcals  23 Carbohydrates 17 Fat 30 Protein  10 Fiber 703 Sodium

title: Cellucor Cor Fetti High Protein Cheesecake
description:
Perfect, macro-friendly alternative for real cheesecake. And it's right around the holidays!

Ingredients: 
4oz Fat Free Cream Cheese
6g Stevia
1.5 Servings Sugar Free Jello
½ Scoop Cellucor Whey (Cor Fetti)
1 Cup Fat Free Greek Yogurt 
1 Cup Pumpkin
1 egg (or ½ Cup Liquid Egg Whites)
Dash of Cinnamon
1 tsp Vanilla Extract

Directions: 
Start by preheating your oven to 350 degrees.
Next, spray down your cooking dish with non stick cooking spray.

Take 4oz of Cream Cheese, 6g of stevia, and your egg (or egg whites) and beat them in a mixing bowl. Next, add in your pumpkin, greek yogurt, Cellucor Whey, Sugar Free jello, cinnamon, and other flavorings and whisk until you get the "cheesecake batter". 

Put into the dish and bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes, and ENJOY!

Serve with Ice Cream, additional yogurt, or top with syrup/peanut butter!

*Let cool overnight for a better tasting cheesecake*

Macros (Whole Cheesecake) (without toppings):
417 kcals 38 Carbohydrates 2 Fat 62 Protein 1 1,17
 Sodium

title: Homemade Almond Butter!
description:
Ingredients:
6-8oz of Almonds (Depending on size of food processor)
Cinnamon
Stevia
Unsweetened baking coco 
Pinch of salt


Start by preheating your oven at 350 (if you want your nuts toasted), you can always do this raw. But I personally believe that roasting them brings out the natural oil and speeds up the processing process.
Next put your almonds in the oven for 10-12 minutes (until you can smell them). After that, grind them until they become a powder. 

Scrape down the sides with a rubber spatula and continue grinding. Then add in your stevia, baking coco, spices, salt, etc. And grind until incorporated. Continue grinding until you get your nut butter!

Enjoy!


Feel free to comment/like/subscribe if you enjoyed the video!

title: High Protein White Chocolate Chip Fudge (simple recipe)
description:
Ingredients:
- 1 Cup Non fat greek yogurt
- 1/2 Cup Canned Pumpkin
- White Chocolate Chips 
- 3 tablespoons baking coco 
- 1/2 Packet Sugar Free Jello Mix 
- 1/2 Cup Stevia 

Optional: 
- Peanut butter 
- Protein Powder 

Start by taking the greek yogurt and and pumpkin and putting it in a bowl, and then simply add in your dry ingredients. 

Once everything is incorporated, sprinkle white chocolate chips on top and take the mixture and put onto a cookie sheet and place in the freezer for 3-4 hours until frozen. 

Enjoy!

title: Spaghetti Squash "Pasta"
description:
Ingredients:
- Spaghetti Squash
- Canned/Fresh Tomatoes
- Cheese 

Optional:
Garlic Salt
Spices



Start by preheating your oven to 375 degrees. Next, take your squash and cut it in half, and scoop out all of the seeds. Next, place the squash in the oven for between 55-60 minutes (until it's cooked fully). 

Finally, take the squash and scoop out the "flesh" (which is a "Spaghetti like consistency) and put onto a plate and top with whatever you desire! I use cheese, canned tomatoes, and a pinch of garlic salt. 

Enjoy!
